<span class="pagesubheading">What Constitutes Sexual Harassment?</span>
<img src="<?php echo $root?>images/h2.png" width="100%" /></p>
<p>Each such incident (of harassment) results in violation of the fundamental rights of &quot;<b>gender equality</b>&quot; and the &quot;<b>right to life and liberty</b>&quot;. It is a clear violation of the rights under Articles 14, 15 and 21 of the Constitution. One of the logical consequences of such an incident is also the violation of the victims fundamental right under Article 19 (1)(g) &lsquo;to practice any profession or to carry out any occupation, trade or business&prime;. Such violations, therefore, attract remedy under Article 32 for the enforcement of these fundamental rights of women.</p><p> Any unwelcome or unwanted sexually determined behaviour (physical,verbal or non verbal contact) violating any woman's dignity comes under sexual harassment. It also includes 
gender based discrimination.<p></br></p></p>
<p><span class="pagesubheading">Who can approach the cell?</span>
<img src="<?php echo $root?>images/h2.png" width="100%" />
</p><p>Any woman employee or female student of NIT Jamshedpur.<p></br></p></p>
<p><span class="pagesubheading">How to lodge a complaint ?</span>
<img src="<?php echo $root?>images/h2.png" width="100%" />
</p><p>The person concerned can contact personally /through phone/write Email to any member of the cell. The identity of the concerned person will remain confidential.</p>
<p>Care would be taken to handle the issue in a sensitive manner and dignity of the person will be protected.</p>
